Goal: Solve the task with a senior-engineer persona prompt but without PL checkpoints

flow:
  prompt: You are a senior software engineer pairing with a junior developer. Read TASK.md and the implementation/test files, but do not read or modify verify.js. Identify ambiguity and risk, write appropriate tests, implement the smallest safe change, run npm test and node verify.js, repair failures, and summarize residual risks. This is a persona-only control arm: do the work directly without relying on structured PL checkpoints beyond the verification loops in this baseline.
  until command_succeeded max 3
    run: npm test [timeout 300]
    if command_failed
      prompt: npm test failed. As the senior engineer, diagnose the failure and make the smallest safe repair. Test output: ${last_stdout} ${last_stderr}
    end
  end
  until command_succeeded max 3
    run: node verify.js [timeout 300]
    if command_failed
      prompt: The verifier failed. As the senior engineer, diagnose the failure and make the smallest safe repair. Verifier output: ${last_stdout} ${last_stderr}
    end
  end

done when:
  gate tests_pass: npm test
  gate oracle_passes: node verify.js
